main_text: イエローカレーペーストとココナッツミルクをたっぷり使ったシーフードカレーとシシカバブ風焼肉、ソムタム、マンゴーココナッツミルクプリンで、初夏のエスニックランチを作りました。豚細切れを竹串に巻きシシカバブ風にしたり、ソムタムに青パパイヤでなく切り干し大根を使っていたことには驚きました。切り干し大根は違和感なく食べることが出来ました。何時ものことながら、どれも美味しく頂きました。😊#イエローカレーペースト #ココナッツミルク #シーフードカレー #シシカバブ #焼肉 #ソムタム #マンゴーココナッツミルクプリン #初夏 #エスニックランチ #青パパイヤ #切り干し大根 #美味しいI made an early summer ethnic lunch with seafood curry with plenty of yellow curry paste and coconut milk shishikabab-style grilled meat somtam and mango coconut milk pudding. I was surprised that the shredded pork was wrapped around a bamboo skewer to make it look like shish kebab and that the somtam used was dried daikon instead of green papaya. I was able to eat the dried daikon without any discomfort. All of them were delicious as always. 😊#Yellow curry paste #Coconut milk #Seafood curry #Shishikabab #Grilled meat #Somtam #Mango coconut milk pudding #Early summer #Ethnic lunch #Blue papaya #Kiriboshi daikon #delicious

main_text: Fun fact I was taking a risk with this review. I’m extremely sensitive to caffeine. My heart goes insane my breathing gets shallow it’s just bad all around. But I love the flavor of coffee! So I was just praying there wasn’t too much caffeine in this flavor 😂!It has the classic date/oat flavor that all mush have.Usually I don’t enjoy the coconut milk based mush flavors because I get a really creamy almost cream cheese flavor from them. That was not the case here. Besides it being a little thicker I couldn’t tell this wasn’t an almond milk based flavor. That also means no coconut flavor which I did miss a little.The coffee flavor was great. A true cold brew coffee flavor. But it was pretty subtle. I honestly didn’t taste it in every bite. So while I liked the flavor I wish it was stronger.And I’m happy to report there were no adverse reactions associated with this review. Thank you mush for keeping the caffeine content in check!This definitely isn’t one of my favorite mush flavors but if you like mush in general I think it’s worth trying out.#overnightoats #breakfast #oats #coffee #coconut #mush #snack #food #foodreview
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "outoftheparkeats"  "comment_text": "Fun fact  I was taking a risk with this review. I’m extremely sensitive to caffeine. My heart goes insane  my breathing gets shallow  it’s just bad all around. But I love the flavor of coffee! So I was just praying there wasn’t too much caffeine in this flavor 😂!

It has the classic date/oat flavor that all mush have.

Usually  I don’t enjoy the coconut milk based mush flavors because I get a really creamy  almost cream cheese flavor from them. That was not the case here. Besides it being a little thicker  I couldn’t tell this wasn’t an almond milk based flavor. That also means no coconut flavor  which I did miss a little.

The coffee flavor was great. A true cold brew coffee flavor. But it was pretty subtle. I honestly didn’t taste it in every bite. So while I liked the flavor  I wish it was stronger.

And I’m happy to report there were no adverse reactions associated with this review. Thank you mush for keeping the caffeine content in check!

This definitely isn’t one of my favorite mush flavors  but if you like mush in general I think it’s worth trying out.

main_text: We have 7 tasty flavors for you to try on this week’s menu!!Burgundy (v) - This vegan sorbet starts with a blueberry base and then we layer in a homemade chardonnay jam.Burlap (v) - This vegan gelato continues to be one of the most requested and popular flavors on our menu. It is made with coconut milk instead of regular milk. The creaminess from the peanut butter mixed with little chunks of melted dark chocolate is reminiscent of Reese's Pieces.Cashmere - From our very first menu when we opened An's in 2018 Cashmere is a goat cheese & honey gelato that is creamy and sweet. Enough said.Cotton - Cotton starts with a cinnamon rice pudding base similar to horchata and blended to our signature creamy texture. Some say it tastes like milk after you eat a bowl of cinnamon toast crunch.Fluff - We use an award-winning wildflower honey to create a sweet gelato base & then swirl it with a homemade blueberry jam.Mohair - We start by making a brown sugar and butter based sauce which gets combined with bananas as we cook them together over a low heat. We then add vanilla and caramel which all gets blended together to create a very smooth and sweet gelato.Brocade - Our brocade gelato is a chocolate lover's dream. It's a chocolate gelato made with 60% cacao chocolate home made brownies (from scratch) and chocolate ganache.#gelato #dessert #icecream #northpark #sandiego #chocolate #brownie #horchata #blueberry #honey #goatcheese #peanutbutter #coconut #caramel #banana
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "ansdrycleaning"  "comment_text": "We have 7 tasty flavors for you to try on this week’s menu!!

Burgundy (v) - This vegan sorbet starts with a blueberry base and then we layer in a homemade chardonnay jam.

Burlap (v) - This vegan gelato continues to be one of the most requested and popular flavors on our menu. It is made with coconut milk instead of regular milk. The creaminess from the peanut butter mixed with little chunks of melted dark chocolate is reminiscent of Reese's Pieces.

Cashmere - From our very first menu when we opened An's in 2018  Cashmere is a goat cheese & honey gelato that is creamy and sweet. Enough said.

Cotton - Cotton starts with a cinnamon rice pudding base  similar to horchata  and blended to our signature creamy texture. Some say it tastes like milk after you eat a bowl of cinnamon toast crunch.

Fluff - We use an award-winning wildflower honey to create a sweet gelato base & then swirl it with a homemade blueberry jam.

Mohair - We start by making a brown sugar and butter based sauce which gets combined with bananas as we cook them together over a low heat. We then add vanilla and caramel which all gets blended together to create a very smooth and sweet gelato.

Brocade - Our brocade gelato is a chocolate lover's dream. It's a chocolate gelato made with 60% cacao chocolate  home made brownies (from scratch)  and chocolate ganache.
